      "comment": "PERCUSSION PRINCE (2) scored at his most recent appearance, getting home by a nose over 1300m at Port Hedland. That continued the solid form this campaign, with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Can measure up again. MISSILE GIRL (3) made progress last time out, finishing 2.25 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1300m at Port Hedland. Has the talent to figure prominently. CHEDDAR BOB (1) scored when resuming two starts ago then was well fancied last time but could only manage fourth over 1406m at Roebourne. Has good early toe so he should be handy in the run. Will be in this for a long way. OSCAR WINNER (6) was safely held last time when he dropped out to finish ninth at Roebourne but down in the weights today. Better than last start and can improve sharply. FRIES WITH THAT (4) won't be far away.",
